VALUES (367, '1 Kettlebell Step Up Video Exercise Guide', 'Quads', 'Strength', 'Kettle Bells', 'Compound',
        'Push (Unilateral)', 'Beginner', 'Abs, Adductors, Calves, Glutes, Hamstrings, Shoulders, Traps, Upper Back', 'The 1 kettlebell step up is a variation of the step up and an exercise used to target the muscles of the leg.
The 1 kettlebell step up challenges the muscles of the quads unilaterally to build balanced strength. It also presents a core challenge as the core fights to stabilize the spine throughout the range of motion.', 'Set up in front of a riser which is 8-12” off the ground.
Hold a kettlebell in one hand and initiate the exercise by stepping on to the riser with one leg.
