Elevating the front foot of the split squat, as seen in the front foot elevated split squat, increases the range of motion of the exercise and places more of an emphasis on the hamstring than the traditional variation.', 'Position a 1-2” riser in front of your foot and set up in a split stance position with your hands by your sides looking straight ahead.
